name: WARUNG BUCU
address: Jalan Raya Pupuan Km. 20, Desa Sanda, Kec. Pupuan, Sanda, Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82163, Indonesia
review 1: Yummiest fish meal. Sitting in a paradise to eat. They farm their own fish. They also have a sweet little cabin overlooking the field that can be rented for $15 a night.
review 2: Very nice place to relax and enjoy nature
review 3: Had the best gurami nyat nyat of all times. Very friendly hosts in a spectacular location surrounded by rice fields and river. Super cheap and super tasty
review 4:
Wow cool little Warung situated on a corner overlooking rice field and a river hear Pupuan on the road over the mountain to Seririt
Climate here is unusually cool for a tropical island due to the elevation

Pak Chef will dish you up some wonderful local food.
They also grow their own coffee which has a unique flavor
review 5: Had a great meal.. very friendly and polite people.. amazing view and atmosphere is great... will come here every trip .. 6 people  very good price
